                      <p
                        id="fs-idp115972800"
                      >Radioisotopes are used in diverse ways to study the mechanisms of chemical reactions in plants and animals. These include labeling fertilizers in studies of nutrient uptake by plants and crop growth, investigations of digestive and milk-producing processes in cows, and studies on the growth and metabolism of animals and plants.</p>

                      <p
                        id="fs-idm4363456"
                      >For example, the radioisotope C-14 was used to elucidate the details of how photosynthesis occurs. The overall reaction is:</p>

                      <div data-type="equation" id="fs-idp161500800">
                        <math display="block">
                          <semantics>
                            <mrow>
                              <mrow>
                                <msub>
